OL,3,CTech companies face new laws if they
OL,4,Cdo not act on stop child explicit
OL,5,Cimages
OL,7,FThe Prime Minister has said that tech
OL,8,Ffirms must introduce controls to
OL,9,F"prevent children from sending and
OL,10,Freceiving sexually explicit images".
OL,12,FSpeaking at the London Tech Week forum
OL,13,Fon Monday morning, Sir Keir Starmer
OL,14,Fsaid that if tech companies do not
OL,15,Fact, then "we will change the law".
OL,17,FStarmer rejected the idea that the
OL,18,F"government is powerless" and said
OL,19,Fthat "when it comes to the safety of
OL,20,Four children, standing by is not an
OL,21,Foption".
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/3
